description:
Bug 38131 - ajc needs -d option while correctly compiling classes from subpackage

I am using ajc 1.1rc1. This is a regression since rc1 and a deviation from javac. I am guessing this may have to do something with change in the underlying Eclipse compiler.

To reproduce the issue, please follow these steps:

1. Create a class in a subpackage such as:

package subpackage;

public class Test {

public static void main(String[] args) {
System.out.println("Hello");
}

}

2. Compile using the following command: ajc -d subpackage\ Test.java

Expected Result: The compiled file should be placed in the existing "subpackage" directory.

Observed Result: A new "subpackage" directory is created under the existing "subpackage" directory, and the compiled file is placed inside it.

It would be nice to have the same behavior as javac.

